"I didn't want my wife to go to Wuhan with me, but she wouldn't get off the bus. "

Recalling the experience of a few days ago, home in Wuxi, Jiangsu Province after 90 truck driver Gu Shifu not only to his wife's shame, more or touched.

On the second night of the Lunar New Year, Gu took on a business: a truck version of the "De de" -- a joint venture of the Amity Foundation Group -- was to donate disinfectant to Wuhan, and had the goods shipped from Huzhou to Wuhan.

The 1,400 km round trip was not a long one for Gu, the veteran driver. He knew the people of Hubei needed the supplies, but his family was worried about his safety and opposed them.

In the end, he convinced his family to take the order. But his wife did not rest assured, insisted on going with him, two people overnight departure, began the first after the Lunar New Year.

Back in Wuxi, he and his wife began 14 days of isolation, leaving their one-year-old daughter in the care of her parents.

"I know Wuhan is an epidemic area, and I came back in quarantine, but I have no regrets, " he told prism on the third day of quarantine.

Also on the same day of the dialogue, at a press conference held on January 30, a spokesman for the Health Commission, Mi Feng, said that according to the current needs of the work to deal with the epidemic, truck drivers transporting supplies to Hubei Province needed to take the necessary protective measures, after return, no fever, cough and other symptoms, allowing them to continue to transport supplies.

The following is the truck driver Gu master's own statement, for the convenience of reading, there are adjustments and deletions.

My wife was so worried, she asked me to take her out with her

My family name is gu, I live in Wuxi, Jiangsu, is a truck driver. On the third day of the Lunar New Year, I drove to Wuhan with my wife to bring disinfectant to the local fire brigade. Now I'm in quarantine at a hotel near my home. I'm fine. After 14 days of quarantine, I can go home with my wife.

On the evening of the second day of the Lunar New Year, I saw someone placing an order on the full APP and wanted to send the goods to Wuhan immediately. This software is similar to Didi. The person who wants to ship the goods places an order on the software, and the driver takes the order.

I called to ask the situation, the other side to be shipped from Huzhou, Zhejiang to Wuhan, is full of Amity Foundation donated to Wuhan Disinfection Water.

I know disinfection water is very important to Wuhan now, but I still have some hesitation, after all, is the epidemic area, so tell him to reply an hour later. At that time, I and my wife, parents, aunt and uncle, as well as one-year-old daughter at home together, ready to rest a few days.

I said the list of things, but the family is very worried, do not agree with me to go to Wuhan.

I remember seeing a short video on the Internet, where volunteers went to Wuhan to give things to help, and they were all pro bono. Now the situation in Wuhan is so critical, the local people need these relief supplies, I think I should go.

Although Wuhan is an epidemic area, but I do not think it is so terrible, there are ten million people, not everyone is infected. Besides, we didn't have much contact in the past. We just unloaded. So I tried to explain it to my family, and I convinced them, and I talked for a long time.

In the end, I took the order. The wife is not at ease, want me to take her out of the car, the daughter temporarily let GRANDPA and grandma help look after. This is the second time I've taken my wife out. Once, years ago, was to Shanghai, a short trip, she happened to be home for nothing.

But this time, up to now, I don't want my wife to go to Wuhan together. Look, I'm going alone, I just have to take care of myself, and I'm more worried about her going with me.

But she did not want to get out of the car, said, "at home worry, rest assured" , or I do not take this single.

I had to. It was so urgent, there was no time to argue, so I took her with me.

January 31,2020, the seventh day of the Lunar New Year. Gu and his wife were quarantined in a government-appointed hotel in Wuxi. In 11 days, the couple will be able to end their isolation and return home to meet their parents and their one-year-old daughter. Photography / Master Koo

The fire department gave five boxes of instant noodles, said there was nothing to serve

When we got our order that night, we immediately drove to Huzhou, took the provincial road for over an hour, and found a place to rest. The third day early in the morning, about eight o'clock delivery, we arrived more than seven o'clock. There's tons of it, hundreds of cases of disinfectant.

January 27,2020, the third day of the Lunar New Year. Gu arrived at the designated loading point in Huzhou, Zhejiang Province, early in the morning, and workers began loading his car with disinfectant. Photography / Master Koo

We had a quick lunch before the lunch load, then drove to Wuhan. A little more than 700 kilometers, about 10 hours of driving, the road is not much, very smooth, to Wuhan is already 9:00 at night.

Single catch is more urgent, originally a friend also suggested that we should wear protective clothing, but temporary hard to buy, we will prepare a few masks, with the past. We didn't have much to eat, and when we got to Huzhou and the shops were open, my wife bought some instant noodles, bread and mineral water.

On the day of his arrival, the city was sealed off. Fortunately, people from the fire brigade met him at the junction of the expressway. We confirmed with the traffic police that we were delivering supplies, and they took photos of our ID cards, took our temperature, and sprayed the cab with disinfectant. After a lot of work, the traffic police put our car into the city.

We had a deal. All I had to do was deliver the goods to the freeway, but unloading at the freeway meant transferring them to the fire truck. There's only two fire trucks out there with limited capacity, so it's GonNa take a long time, till the wee hours.

We agreed, why don't we just get off the highway and go to the warehouse.

The third night after nine o'clock under the highway, and then drove a few kilometers from the highway junction of the warehouse. I got out of the car and helped to untangle the van. The firemen had said they would do it themselves and told us to stay in the cab so we wouldn't get infected. But I tied the scarf myself. I know how.

Remove the cloth, more than a dozen fire officers and soldiers rushed up to start unloading. In the middle of the night, they stand in a line, one by one, and in half an hour they unload into the warehouse. UNLOADED CARGO, have no rest, they directly took a pile of disinfection water out disinfection, very hard.

Wuhan, the situation is urgent, so we are not allowed to stay long, after unloading we prepare for the night on the highway.

Before leaving, the fire brigade, specially to the cab, gave me and my wife five boxes of instant noodles, said Wuhan now nothing to entertain, let us take some instant noodles pad stomach. Now that Wuhan is so short of supplies, they give me things.

On the highway, the traffic police again check identity card, temperature, confirmed that there is no problem before you leave.

Leaving Wuhan, we walked to the Qichun County Service area, the day before overnight to Huzhou, that night is too tired, in the service area parking to sleep one night, the next day to drive back to Wuxi.

I heard that I was not the only car to go to Wuhan, but because of the platform to receive orders, drivers everywhere, we can not contact each other. I know a master from Linyi, Shandong Province, who went to Wuhan from Yancheng, a city in Jiangsu Province.

14 days in isolation, you can't see your kids and you wonder

I came back off the highway, and I started taking his temperature.

The government says they're quarantining them because they're from the hot zone. We'll be quarantined at the designated hotel for 14 days, until February 11th.

On the fifth day, the second day of the official quarantine, my dad brought over supplies and a change of clothes. It's right next door, but we can't see our families. Take it to the lobby and have it transferred by the paramedics.

We didn't know we were being quarantined until we got back. All those who return from Hubei will be quarantined, and I reported this to the Manbang Gang.

FULL HELP COMFORT US say: "This you rest assured, come back to settle, the isolation of the loss of delay, full will be subsidized. " In fact, this time, as long as almost done, and no one will care. They said they would be responsible for the driver.

Now we eat, breakfast, lunch and dinner are on time staff to the door, at the door, we take our own room.

We also asked how to pay, the staff said that in these extraordinary times, the government did not explicitly say, eat first, do not worry about money. The Man Gang said that if there were any further expenses, they would reimburse them accordingly.

When I checked into the hotel, there were already a few people in quarantine up ahead, and I'm guessing there were dozens of people in our town. There's a lot of quarantine points. Our town, the next town, they all have designated ones.

Isolation's no fun. If you can't get out, you just have to brush it. Sometimes I would video chat with my kids, and I would make a phone call in my spare time, thinking even if I couldn't see my kids. She's fine at home. She's fine with my parents. Now more than a year old, has been jogging, still learning to speak, sometimes called "Mom and Dad" , sometimes not happy to call.

My wife came back with a cough and a fever, and I was worried. I went to the hospital to have a check-up. It's nothing. I think I have a cold.

I Know Wuhan is an epidemic area, but I have no regrets

I was born in 1996 and have been working for eight years since 2012. My wife was two years younger than I was, and after our marriage we had a daughter, who is now more than a year old.

When I first started working, I worked as a handyman in the factory, and then I studied to be a cook for two years. I was young. I didn't study very hard. My father is also a truck driver, before the long distance, from Wuxi to Guangdong, a person sports car is too hard, let me come back to help, on the road good have a look after, I also came back, began to learn sports car.

Then I bought a car and started running on my own. My Dad still drives sports cars, but he doesn't do long-distance, mostly short.

I have a 6.8 m JAC medium truck, usually in southern Jiangsu, northern Zhejiang and Shanghai. I'm not too picky. I'll take any job that comes with a car. The car had been in the market for more than a year, at a cost of a little over two hundred thousand, with a $100,000 down payment, a $100,000 loan, and interest payments of more than $5,000 a month, which could be paid off in about two years.

Huzhou, Zhejiang Province, on the third day of the Lunar New Year on January 27,2020. While the workers were busy filling the car with disinfectant, Gu took a Selfie of himself and the truck he had just bought over a year ago. Photography / Master Koo

Now every month to earn money, excluding the car loan, basic can also afford the expenses of the home. If you have some unexpected expenses, swing by a friend. Overall, it was pretty much what I expected at first.

To tell the truth, take this order, the price is also quite attractive, because it is the Spring Festival, coupled with the epidemic, but also empty back, they bid much higher than usual, excluding fuel and tolls, still can earn some. I mean, you have a car to support.

This trip to Wuhan, basically no pit, and I understand the situation is roughly the same, just out of a high-speed mouth, other no big problem. I Know Wuhan is an epidemic area, came back and quarantined, but I have no regrets.

When I first started working, I worked as a handyman in the factory, and then I studied to be a cook for two years. I was young. I didn't study very hard. My father is also a truck driver, before the long distance, from Wuxi to Guangdong, a person sports car is too hard, let me come back to help, on the road good have a look after, I also came back, began to learn sports car.

Then I bought a car and started running on my own. My Dad still drives sports cars, but he doesn't do long-distance, mostly short.

I have a 6.8 m JAC medium truck, usually in southern Jiangsu, northern Zhejiang and Shanghai. I'm not too picky. I'll take any job that comes with a car.
